<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="499" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,488,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">Description. Male imago.</emphasis>
Length: body, 
<quantity box="[653,753,152,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.23" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" unit="mm" value="3.23">3.23 mm</quantity>
; forewings, 
<quantity box="[886,986,152,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.83" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" unit="mm" value="2.83">2.83 mm</quantity>
. General coloration: thorax chestnut, legs and abdomen whitish with greyish marks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">Head:</emphasis>
yellowish tinged with black on hind and front margin, antennae pale. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1025,1119,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">Thorax:</emphasis>
pronotum yellow pale tinged completely with black except for two median bands (
<figureCitation box="[751,847,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Macunahyphes eduardoi sp. nov. (Ephemeroptera, Leptohyphidae). Male imago. Figure 1. Forewing. Figure 2. Detail of elongated projections of penes (ventral view). Figure 3. Habitus (dorsal view, scale 1 mm). Figure 4. Genitalia (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
Figure 
<number box="[833,847,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), prosternum yellow pale tinged slightly with black. Mesonotum chestnut tinged with grey and suture tinged with grey; mesosternum yellowish chestnut. Metanotum chestnut with anterior region tinged with grey; metasternum yellow tinged slightly with gray. Legs: coxae and trochanters yellowish tinged with grey; femora yellowish with base tinged with grey and anterior region with black band; tibia and tarsi grayish. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[493,588,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Macunahyphes eduardoi sp. nov. (Ephemeroptera, Leptohyphidae). Male imago. Figure 1. Forewing. Figure 2. Detail of elongated projections of penes (ventral view). Figure 3. Habitus (dorsal view, scale 1 mm). Figure 4. Genitalia (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
Figure 
<number box="[575,588,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
): forewing translucent with costal and subcostal area tinged with grey; hind wings absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[303,424,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">Abdomen:</emphasis>
terga I-VII pale tinged with grey; terga VIII-X pale yellow tinged with grey. Genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Macunahyphes eduardoi sp. nov. (Ephemeroptera, Leptohyphidae). Male imago. Figure 1. Forewing. Figure 2. Detail of elongated projections of penes (ventral view). Figure 3. Habitus (dorsal view, scale 1 mm). Figure 4. Genitalia (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
Figure 
<number box="[151,168,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
): styliger plate and penes opaque yellow, forceps whitish; styliger plate projected posteriorly as columnar base; penes wide, with pair of elongated projections with small, hook-shaped lateral expansions distributed from its base to middle region (
<figureCitation box="[233,327,533,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,496,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Macunahyphes eduardoi sp. nov. (Ephemeroptera, Leptohyphidae). Male imago. Figure 1. Forewing. Figure 2. Detail of elongated projections of penes (ventral view). Figure 3. Habitus (dorsal view, scale 1 mm). Figure 4. Genitalia (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="499">
Figure 
<number box="[311,327,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="499" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral filaments tinged with grey, except at joints; terminal filament pale with base grey at joints.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
